BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pUNjUYIbunJlqgVLLeKsh
SUMMARY:Hasan Raheem
DTSTAMP:20260409T031154Z
DTSTART:20260415T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Neumos Presents  HASAN RAHEEM with Special Guests! TUE\, 14 APR
	 2026 at 07:00PM PDT Ages: All Ages to Enter\, 21 & Over to Drink Doors Op
	en: 07:00PM OnSale: Fri\, 30 Jan 2026 at 10:00AM PST Announcement: Mon\, 2
	6 Jan 2026 at 07:00AM PST Hey\, I’m Hasan. I grew up in Gilgit\, surrounde
	d by mountains and quiet moments. Eventually\, life brought me to Karachi\
	, where I thought I'd just study medicine and figure things out as I went.
	 Honestly\, I didn't plan on any of this—music was just something I loved 
	doing after class\, a way to unwind\, write down feelings\, and jam with f
	riends. Fast forward a bit\, and now I'm touring the world\, playing shows
	 from the US to the UK\, and finding myself in places I never imagined. It
	's genuinely been wild seeing people connect to my songs—something that st
	arted out as a personal outlet becoming something bigger\, shared\, and me
	aningful. But no matter how many stages I step onto or cities I visit\, I'
	m still that same guy who scribbles lyrics in notebooks\, stays up late ch
	asing new melodies\, and just tries to keep things real. My sound is a mix
	 of everything—R&B\, hip-hop\, indie pop—because that's what feels true to
	 me. I love experimenting with different vibes\; some days I'll drop somet
	hing chill\, other days I'll create a track that you can't help but dance 
	to. At the end of the day\, music for me is about connection—connecting to
	 you\, connecting to myself\, and telling stories that matter. It's cool k
	nowing we're all experiencing life through music together\, each song beco
	ming part of our shared story. Important Information: \\* This event is al
	l ages. Valid ID is required to enter bar areas. \\* Doors open at the lis
	ted event time. \\* Event start time is generally one hour after doors ope
	n but is subject to change without notice. \\* All tickets are nonrefundab
	le with the exception of event cancellation. \\* Support acts are subject 
	to change. \\* Orders in violation of the published ticket limit are subje
	ct to cancellation without notice.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/
